{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bc9e2c15-15a4-4bfc-884e-de28b4badb26","content":"In .NET MAUI, you configure platform lifecycle events in your `MauiProgram.cs` using `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* runs on pause */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* runs on stop */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* runs on background */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code separated\n- The delegates receive the native platform object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS)\n- Other available Android events: `OnCreate`, `OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, `OnRestart`\n- Other available iOS events: `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate`, `OnActivated`, `OnResignActivation`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"248ca908-bd27-4110-8fe3-c51a1ab00a37","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":366,"requestId":"D44B:29787D:1CE6C8B:207A7D2:6A07C196"},"id":"5651c7f2-11b9-41a6-82e8-e498d2fb4944","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:00:14.071Z","parentId":"0f4c7605-3732-4563-b845-684cc975d58f"}
